  <h2>Why We Built This</h2>

  <p>Claude Code is great, but it ties you to your desk. If you're using the CLI, you need a terminal open. If you're using VS Code, you need VS Code open. Step away and you lose visibility.</p>

  <p>We wanted something different:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>Server-owned processes</strong> &mdash; Claude runs on your dev machine. Client disconnects don't interrupt work. Pick up where you left off on any device.</li>
    <li><strong>Multi-session dashboard</strong> &mdash; See all your projects at once. No more cycling through terminal tabs or VS Code windows.</li>
    <li><strong>Mobile supervision</strong> &mdash; Push notifications for approvals. Respond from your phone. Keep your agents productive while you're away.</li>
    <li><strong>File uploads from anywhere</strong> &mdash; Share screenshots, images, and documents directly from your phone's camera roll.</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>How the Public Relay Works</h2>

  <p>The relay solves a fundamental problem: your dev machine is behind a firewall, but you want to access it from your phone on cellular data.</p>

  <p>Previously, you needed Tailscale, ngrok, port forwarding, or a VPN. Now you just enable the relay:</p>

  <div class="code-block">
    <code>npm i -g yepanywhere</code><br>
    <code>yepanywhere</code><br>
    <code># Open Settings &rarr; Enable "Public Relay"</code>
  </div>

  <p>Your server connects to <code>relay.yepanywhere.com</code> and gets a unique URL. Open that URL on your phone and you're in.</p>

  <div class="feature-highlight">
    <h4>End-to-End Encrypted</h4>
    <p>All traffic is encrypted using SRP-6a key exchange and TweetNaCl. The relay can't see your code, your conversations, or your files. We only see encrypted blobs passing through.</p>
  </div>

  <p>No accounts are required. No Firebase, no database, no tracking. Your password never leaves your device&mdash;it's only used to derive encryption keys locally.</p>

  <h2>Full Feature Set</h2>

  <p>Beyond remote access, Yep Anywhere gives you:</p>

  <ul>
    <li><strong>Real-time streaming</strong> &mdash; Watch Claude think and work, just like in the terminal</li>
    <li><strong>Tool approval</strong> &mdash; Approve or reject tool requests from your phone</li>
    <li><strong>File uploads</strong> &mdash; Share images, screenshots, and documents from any device</li>
    <li><strong>Push notifications</strong> &mdash; Get notified when your agent needs attention (uses VAPID, no third-party services)</li>
    <li><strong>Voice input</strong> &mdash; Talk to your agents via browser speech API</li>
    <li><strong>Session management</strong> &mdash; Star important sessions, archive old ones, filter and search</li>
    <li><strong>Interop</strong> &mdash; See sessions started in Claude CLI or VS Code in real-time</li>
    <li><strong>Diff viewer</strong> &mdash; Review code changes with syntax highlighting</li>
    <li><strong>Todo tracking</strong> &mdash; See Claude's task list and progress</li>
  </ul>

