  <h2>Getting Started</h2>

  <p>Installation takes about 30 seconds:</p>

  <div class="code-block">
    <code># Install from npm</code><br>
    <code>npm i -g yepanywhere</code><br><br>
    <code># Start the server</code><br>
    <code>yepanywhere</code><br><br>
    <code># Open http://localhost:3400</code><br>
    <code># Go to Settings &rarr; Enable "Public Relay"</code><br>
    <code># Set a username and password for remote access</code>
  </div>

  <p>Once configured, go to <a href="https://yepanywhere.com/remote"><strong>yepanywhere.com/remote</strong></a> on your phone or any device. Enter your username and password, and you're connected.</p>

  <div class="cta-section" style="margin: 24px 0;">
    <h3>Ready to Connect?</h3>
    <p>If you've already set up your server, log in now:</p>
    <a href="https://yepanywhere.com/remote" class="btn btn-primary">Go to Remote Login</a>
  </div>

  <h3>Requirements</h3>
  <ul>
    <li>Node.js 18+</li>
    <li>Claude Code CLI installed and authenticated (or an Anthropic API key)</li>
    <li>That's it</li>
  </ul>

  <h2>Privacy & Security</h2>

  <p>We take privacy seriously:</p>
  <ul>
    <li><strong>End-to-end encryption</strong> &mdash; The relay can't read your data</li>
    <li><strong>No accounts</strong> &mdash; No email, no signup, no tracking</li>
    <li><strong>Runs locally</strong> &mdash; All your data stays on your machine</li>
    <li><strong>Open source</strong> &mdash; <a href="https://github.com/kzahel/yepanywhere">100% MIT licensed</a>, audit it yourself</li>
    <li><strong>Self-host option</strong> &mdash; Run your own relay if you prefer</li>
  </ul>

  <p>The only thing we store is the encrypted connection state while you're connected. When you disconnect, it's gone.</p>

  <h2>What's Next</h2>

  <p>We're actively developing Yep Anywhere. Some things we're working on:</p>
  <ul>
    <li>Remote executors &mdash; run Claude on VMs or containers via SSH</li>
    <li>Better notification controls</li>
    <li>Session sharing (with permission)</li>
    <li>More agent providers (Codex, local models)</li>
  </ul>

  <p>If you have feature requests or find bugs, <a href="https://github.com/kzahel/yepanywhere/issues">open an issue on GitHub</a>.</p>

